message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Somaliland, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Bicycling: If you have a bicycle, it can be a convenient and faster way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 3-5 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public transportation: Check if there are any local buses or minibusses available that can take you to the grocery store. Inquire with locals or at nearby bus stops for information on routes and schedules.

4. Taxi or ride-sharing services: If you prefer a more comfortable and convenient option, you can hire a taxi or use ride-sharing services like Uber or Bolt. These services are usually available in urban areas and can take you directly to the grocery store.

Consider the availability, cost, and convenience of each option before deciding which one suits you best.
